### Description

Because "this" can not be accessed in the constructor before the super() call.

For this case:
```
abstract class X {
   constructor(protected readonly url: string) {
   }
}

class Y extends X {
   constructor(@Inject(ACCOUNT_URL_TOKEN) url: string) {
      super(url);
   }
}
```
Replacing to
```
class Y extends X {
   apiUrl = inject(ACCOUNT_URL_TOKEN);
   constructor() {
      super(this.apiUrl);
   }
}
```
gives an error:
```
TS17009: super must be called before accessing this in the constructor of a derived class.
```

